Yes, I feel good about the 5D code direction. The main thing it accomplished is important: templates now get a real context, .j2 files can use real Jinja2, and bad variables fail clearly instead of silently generating wrong Kickstarts.

The one caveat: 5D supports whole-file Jinja templates, but not reusable Jinja include/partial files yet. That is the next step.

