About the different Kickstart pieces

You are not misunderstanding. Eventually the Kickstart should not be one giant repeated file for every profile. The clean design is:

content/
  profiles/
    50-minimal.yml
    20-security-baseline.yml
    10-developer-workstation.yml
  ks/
    rhel8-minimal.ks.j2
    rhel9-minimal.ks.j2
    rhel10-minimal.ks.j2
    profiles/
      rhel8-developer-workstation.ks.j2
      rhel9-developer-workstation.ks.j2
      rhel8-security-baseline.ks.j2
      rhel9-security-baseline.ks.j2
    partials/
      header.ks.j2
      network-dhcp.ks.j2
      root-password.ks.j2
      storage-lvm.ks.j2
      packages-minimal.ks.j2
      packages-developer.ks.j2
      services-basic.ks.j2
      post-aerolit.ks.j2

But your current 5D code does not support {% include %} yet, because it renders Jinja from a raw string. For includes/partials to work, the next phase should add a Jinja2 FileSystemLoader pointed at the template folders.

So I would make 5E:

Phase 5E — Add Jinja2 template library / partial support

That means:

* Support {% include "partials/network-dhcp.ks.j2" %}.
* Support templates under subdirectories like profiles/rhel8-developer-workstation.ks.j2.
* Add starter partial files.
* Convert the minimal template to use those partials.
* Keep generated /ks/*.ks as output only.

Then Phase 6 stays what we said before: overrides and emergency edit behavior.